headline: Warren Buffett Says Buy This S&P 500 Index Fund -- It Could Soar 156% by 2030, According to a Top Wall Street Analyst
summary: Warren Buffett has steered the Berkshire Hathaway holding company to market-crushing returns for 59 years.  Buffett has some basic advice for investors looking for success in the stock market: Buy an index fund that tracks the S&P 500.  The Vanguard S&P 500 ETF is one of the cheapest options, and a top Wall Street analyst thinks it could soar 156% by 2030.
